\int^\pi_{-\pi}
|\cos| \text{ and } |\sin| 
\int^\pi_{-\pi} (2-|x|) \cos(x) = 4 \text{ and } \int^\pi_{-\pi} |\sin(x)| = 4
[-\pi, \pi]
f(x)=(2-|x|) \cos(x)
I=[-\pi,\pi]
\int_I f(x)dx=2\color{blue}{\int_0^{\pi}(2-x)\cos(x)dx}=2\times\color{blue}{2}
\int^\pi_{-\pi} (2-|x|) \cos(x)dx=\int^{0}_{-\pi} (2+x) \cos(x)dx+ \int^\pi_{0} (2-x) \cos(x)dx
\int^\pi_{-\pi} (2-|x|) \cos(x)\,dx=2\int^\pi_0 (2-x) \cos(x)\,dx
\int^\pi_{-\pi} (2-|x|) \cos(x)\,dx=4
